{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"43a413cf-05d4-4112-ba5d-2aa724d62148","content":"The directory is empty — there's no project yet. No worries, here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish a .NET tool to NuGet:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n\n    <!-- These make it a dotnet tool -->\n    <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n    <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n    <!-- NuGet package metadata -->\n    <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n    <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n    <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n    <Description>An MCP server using stdio transport.</Description>\n    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n    <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n| Property | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `PackAsTool` | Marks the project as a .NET global/local tool |\n| `ToolCommandName` | The CLI command users invoke (e.g. `my-mcp-server`) |\n| `OutputType=Exe` | Required — tools must be executables |\n\n### Publish workflow\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run it with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server          # runs via stdio\n```\n\nThe two essential properties are **`PackAsTool`** and **`ToolCommandName`** — everything else is standard NuGet metadata. Since your server uses stdio transport, it works naturally as a dotnet tool with no additional configuration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"af090a01-97ac-4a72-8480-3bfe366ae855","outputTokens":572},"id":"2502748b-2276-496d-ad7f-66e5d222d529","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:43:33.521Z","parentId":"17ad5da4-a23a-4d4d-9e4d-1a2173010a2c"}
